content: Brydon Carse bowls this full again, on off, Rovman Powell knocks it to long off for one. ENGLAND WIN BY 37 RUNS!
Pitched up and around off, Rovman Powell drills it to long off and comes back for the second run.

BOWLED'EM? Or is it? Uh..oh! Brydon Carse almost had the last laugh, but he has overstepped again. This is a good yorker, on middle. Rovman Powell backs away to carve it away, but is late to put his bat down as the ball goes under his bat to rattle the stumps. As soon as he starts to walk back, the umpire calls him back as this is a No Ball. Disappointment for Carse, but another Free Hit is coming up.

FOUR! Much more in control! Brydon Carse bowls this short again and on middle. Rovman Powell is expecting that and steps back early. He swivels and hammers it to the deep square leg fence for another boundary.
FOUR! Balls flying everywhere! Back of a length and on off, cross-seam delivery, Rovman Powell has a wild swing at it. Gets a top edge that goes over the keeper's head for four more runs. 200 up!

FOUR! Streaky! Tries the yorker but just misses it, on middle, angling in. Rovman Powell tries to flick but loses his bottom hand. The ball goes off the leading edge and flies over short third for a boundary.
SIX! Up, up and away! Brydon Carse goes fuller but angling into the pads. Rovman Powell picks it up, brings his wrists into play and whips it over the deep square leg fence for a biggie.
Fuller and around off, Rovman Powell drives it to sweeper covers. Well, the umpire signals that it is a No Ball for overstepping. Free Hit up next...
Wow...you don't see this too often in T20Is! A googly, full and on off, turns away, Akeal Hosein decides to leave it alone. Looks at Rashid and smiles.
Quicker, short and on leg, Rovman Powell backs away to work it away but misses as the ball goes off his pads to short third. A leg bye is taken.
Slows it up, full but down the leg side, Rovman Powell lets it go. Wided.
Flighted, full and on off, Rovman Powell pushes it to sweeper covers for a couple of more runs.

SIX! Just over! Another short ball, on middle, Rovman Powell rocks back and heaves it away. The ball flies hard and flat towards deep mid-wicket. Jacob Bethell runs to his righ, leaps and gets his hands on it but the momentum takes the ball over the ropes for a biggie.

FIFTY FOR POWELL! A bright spot in an otherwise disappointing performance from the team. His 9th in T20Is and he is continuing his good form here. Short again and on middle, Rovman Powell backs away and punches it through covers for a brace.
Floated, short and on middle, turns away, Rovman Powell pulls it away to deep mid-wicket but denies the single.
Change of pace, touch fuller and on off, Rovman Powell pushes it through covers for one. Luke Wood finishes a nice spell with figures of 4-0-31-3.
Good length and on middle, Akeal Hosein nudges it to square leg for one.

OUT! TAKEN! Luke Wood with the double strike in the over! He bangs this into the pitch again, but pace on this time. Gudakesh Motie stays back and looks to pull but the ball gets big on him. It goes off the top edge towards long on where Will Jacks runs forward a bit to his right and takes a fine sliding catch. England are just 2 wickets away from the whitewash!
Gudakesh Motie c W Jacks b L Wood 1 (2b 0x4 0x6)
Back of a length and on off, slower again, Rovman Powell goes through his pull early and cue-ends it towards mid off for a run.
Slower one, full and on middle, dipping in, Gudakesh Motie drills it to long on for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Luke Wood gets his second wicket here! He lands this short of a length and into the body of the batter. Jason Holder tries to pull it away but gets a bit cramped up and only manages a top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards deep square leg where Brydon Carse moves a bit to his left and takes the catch. That's the end of Holder's nice little cameo.
Jason Holder c B Carse b L Wood 25 (12b 0x4 3x6)
Ouch! Flighted, full and on middle, Rovman Powell goes for the slog but gets it from the toe-end of the bat. The ball skids across the pitch and hits Holder on the other end.
Quicker, short and on middle, Jason Holder swats it towards long on for one.

SIX! Into the crowd! Drops it short and around off. Jason Holder rocks back to heave it away but gets nowhere near the ball. However, he uses his long handle to connect and dispatches it over the wide long on fence for a biggie.
Floated, full and on middle, Rovman Powell uses his feet to take it on the full and knocks it to long on for a single.
Shorter in length and outside off, Rovman Powell cuts it hard but finds point.
Beaten! Tossed up, full and on off, turns away, Rovman Powell goes down for the slog sweep but fails to connect.
Hard length and on off, Rovman Powell dabs it to point for one. 85 needed in 24.

SIX! Going, going, gone! Brydon Carse digs it into the pitch, on middle, does not bounce that much. Rovman Powell picks up the length early, rocks back and pulls it with disdain over the deep square leg fence for half a dozen more.
Swing and a miss! Short of a length and on off, Rovman Powell has wild swing at it but misses.
Hits the length hard, on middle, angling in, Rovman Powell gets cramped up for room and blocks it out.
FOUR! Sheer power! Rovman Powell is putting on a show! Pitched up and just around off, Powell backs away a bit, gets under it and thumps it between mid off and extra covers for another boundary.
FOUR! Powered away! Back of a length and outside off, Rovman Powell stands tall and smacks it over extra covers for a boundary. 150 up for WI!
Quicker, short and on off, Jason Holder winds up for the scoop, but adjusts and paddles it through square leg for a brace.

SIX! Just over! Flighted, full and on middle, Jason Holder takes it on and slogs it towards the long on fence again. Will Jacks thinks he is in the game, leaps up and gets fingertips on it, but only to parry it over for a six.
Short and on off, Rovman Powell punches it through covers for a run.
FOUR! Nicely done! Flatter, short and around off, Rovman Powell shuffles across and scoops it over the keeper's head for a boundary.

Put down! A terrific effort, though! Floated, full and on middle, Jason Holder uses his feet and lofts it flat and aerially towards long on. Will Jacks once again runs forward, puts a dive in and gets both hands on the ball just as the ball dies in, but it just spills out. A single taken.
SIX! Gets hold of this one! Tossed up, full and on middle, in the slot as well. Jason Holder just takes his front foot out of the way and dispatches it over the long on fence for a biggie.

Uppish but safe! Short again and on middle, Jason Holder looks to pull but mistimes it high in the air towards long on. Ben Duckett comes running forward, slides in but the ball still drops well in front of him. They cross.
Goes short and on leg, Rovman Powell heaves it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Darts this one full and on middle, Rovman Powell drills it hard down the pitch. Liam Dawson gets down on his follow-through and takes another blow to his left hand. Painful!

DROPPED! A very tough chance! Floated up, full and on off, Holder crunches it straight back towards the bowler. Dawson tries to take it near his left knee but the ball is hit extremely hard and it clips him on the fingertips and goes behind. They cross.
Fuller, on off, Jason Holder blocks that one back to the bowler.
Quicker, on the pads, Jason Holder looks to flick but misses it on the inside edge and wears it on the front pad.
FIVE WIDES! Starts with a full ball, down the leg side. Jason Holder gets in a position to paddle but misses it. Jos Buttler behind the wicket fails to gather it, and it runs away for a boundary.
Goes short and on off, Jason Holder punches it through covers for one. Just 2 runs and a wicket off the over!

OUT! TAKEN! A blinder at short covers! Adil Rashid tosses it up nicely, full and on off, turns away a bit. Romario Shepherd, against his instincts, makes room and tries to push it but is way too early into the shot as the ball loops in above his eyes. He only manages to chip it towards short covers where Harry Brook puts in a full-length dive forward to take a spectacular catch inches above the ground. Windies six down now!
Romario Shepherd c H Brook b A Rashid 0 (5b 0x4 0x6)
Just short! Slows it up, shortish and on middle, Romario Shepherd stays back and knocks it down the pitch. It goes uppishly but falls just in front of Rashid.
Tossed up, leg break, on middle and off. Romario Shepherd lunges forward and drives it to cover.
Floated, on the leg stump, Romario Shepherd gets on the backfoot and tucks it to short fine leg.
Tossed up, on the leg stump, Rovman Powell plays it with the soft hands towards square leg for a single.
Short again by Brydon, outside off, Romario Shepherd swings across but does not connect.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Brydon Carse has his revenge! Brydon spots Hope backing away and follows him with a short-of-a-good-length delivery. Hope hops and tries to turn it away with a closed bat face. Closes the bat face early and gets a top edge that goes straight up behind the wicket. The keeper, Jos Buttler takes a few steps in front and does the rest.
Shai Hope (c) c J Buttler b B Carse 45 (27b 3x4 3x6)
Banged into the wicket, slightly away from the batter, Shai Hope attempts the reverse scoop again but fails to connect.
FOUR! Brydon Carse rolls his finger on that one, pitches it on the good length, on the stumps. Shai Hope backs away and clears his front leg to slap it over extra cover for a boundary.
FOUR! Innovation pays off yet again for Hope! At pace, on a length, on off, Hope uses the pace again by setting up for the reverse scoop and executes it nicely over short third for a boundary.
Four!

SIX! Innovative shot from Shai Hope! Brydon Carse starts from over the wicket and lands it a bit short of length, on the stumps. Shai Hope gets in the position and reverse scoops it over third man for six.
Fired in, full and on off, Shai pushes it in front of cover for a quick run.
FOUR! In the gap! Slower through the air, shorter, around off, Shai waits for it before slamming it over extra cover. Jacob Bethell puts in a valiant dive at long off to his left but in vain.
Speared in, flat and short, on off, Hope goes back and plays it back to Dawson.
Flatter, on the stumps, Shai Hope goes for the reverse sweep but hits it straight to the sliding backward point fielder.
Fuller, on the leg stump, Shai Hope gets on the backfoot and punches it past extra cover. Brydon Carse runs to his right from deep cover, dives and cuts it off to a couple of runs.
Starts with a full ball, on middle and off, Rovman Powell makes room for himself and drives it to long off for a single.
Full toss, on the middle and leg, Rovman Powell flicks it to deep mid wicket for a single.
Tossed up, on off, Rovman Powell lunges forward and defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely done! The length is pulled back by Rashid but offers width on off. Rovman feasts on it as he stays back and cuts it through point for a boundary.

FOUR! Brute force! Looped up, full again, on off, Rovman Powell smashes it back past the bowler. Adil Rashid tries to take it to his left but the ball flies past him even before he can get his hands up.
SIX! Muscled into the stands! A bit too full from Adil. Right in the wheelhouse, on off, Powell winds up and smokes it over long on for a biggie.
Starts on a short length, on middle and leg, Rovman Powell uses his feet and chips it to short mid wicket. Powell takes off for a run and is sent back by Shai Hope in time.
Fuller, on the pads, Rovman Powell tucks it to long on for a single.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Fuller and quicker, outside off, Rovman collapses his back knee and drives it square of the wicket to the left of deep cover for a boundary.
Fired in on the pads, Rovman Powell goes for the full-blooded sweep but misses on the inside edge.
Pushed through, short and on off, Hope lofts it back over the bowler's head for a single. Bethell loses his footing on the follow-through.
Short and on off, cut in front of backward point for a single by Rovman.
Short and on off, punched past cover for a single by Hope.
Flatter, on the pads, Rovman Powell punches it from the backfoot to mid-wicket.
Shortish, leg break, Shai Hope works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up, wide outside off, Rovman Powell guides that one through cover for a single.
Fuller, on the leg, Rovman Powell defends.

A loud shout for LBW but turned down! This looks close but England decide against the review. Loopy delivery that drops on the batter, on off, Rovman is beaten by turn as he presents a straight bat to block. The ball spins past the bat to catch him on the back thigh. It rolls past the keeper for a couple of leg byes. Ball Tracking shows that the ball was bouncing over the off stump, so, a wise decision not to go for the review.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Adil Rashid makes an impact straight away! Tossed up from over the wicket, on a nagging length. This turns into the batter and Sherfane Rutherford tries to hit it with the spin. Gets down on a knee for the slog sweep but does not get enough distance to clear the ropes. It is hit towards the longer part of the ground and Luke Wood takes a simple catch at deep backward square leg.
Sherfane Rutherford c L Wood b A Rashid 1 (4b 0x4 0x6)
Tossed up, outside off, Sherfane Rutherford dabs it to backward point for a single.
Fuller, outside off, Sherfane Rutherford guides it to short third and takes off for a single but is sent back by Shai Hope.
Quicker and fuller, drifting into the batter, Sherfane Rutherford punches it to extra cover.

OUT! TAKEN! Jacob Bethell can do no wrong tonight! Shimron Hetmyer's promising stay has been cut short. Pushed across the left-hander from around the wicket by Bethell, on a nagging length, Shimron gets down on a knee for the slog sweep. Ends up dragging it a lot straighter and picks out the man at long on to absolute perfection. Ben Duckett makes no mistake.
Shimron Hetmyer c B Duckett b J Bethell 26 (8b 1x4 3x6)

OUT! c Ben Duckett b Jacob Bethell.
Shimron Hetmyer c B Duckett b J Bethell 26 (8b 1x4 3x6)
Fuller, on off, Shai Hope makes room for himself and works it to covers for a single.
Tossed up, on the off stump, Shai Hope drives that one past covers for a brace.
SIX! That has gone many a mile! Attacking the stumps, on a length, Hetmyer puts on the dancing shoes and thumps it way over deep mid-wicket for six more. West Indies end the Powerplay at 66/2!
SIX! Excellent shot! Angling into the pads, on a length, Shimron Hetmyer walks inside the line of the ball and picks it up over deep fine leg for a six.

Leg bye! Shai Hope shows his cards too early as he backs away. Wood spots that and follows him with a slower one, on a nagging length. Hope misses the flick and a leg bye is taken as the ball goes off the pads to short third.
On off, on a back of a length, nudged to mid-wicket for one more by Shimron.
FOUR! Streaky but they all count! On a shortish length, on off, Shimron Hetmyer swings for the pull but gets a top edge that sails over the leaping the keeper, Jos Buttler for a boundary.
On a nagging length, on middle, Hope works it to mid-wicket and crosses over.
SIX! A shot of authority! Dawson lands it on a nagging length, on middle. Shimron Hetmyer gets down on a knee and clobbers it flat and to the left of the man at deep mid-wicket for a six.
Full and on off, driven past cover for a single by Shai.

Not that far away from going to hand! Pushed across the left-hander, on a nagging length, Hetmyer looks to play it on the rise. Slices it towards extra cover where Harry Brook runs to his left but the ball falls out of his reach. They cross.
Shorter and quicker, on off, Shimron Hetmyer goes on the back foot and tucks it in the vacant mid-wicket region for a couple of runs.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Liam Dawson strikes with his second ball! Nicely slowed down by Dawson and the length is kept away from the batter. Evin is lured into the big shot and is beaten in the flight. He is nowhere near the pitch of the ball but still goes through with the swing. Skies it straight up towards deep mid-wicket where Ben Duckett settles under the skier and snaffles it with ease.
Evin Lewis c B Duckett b L Dawson 9 (6b 0x4 1x6)
Leg bye! Speared in at the pads, Hope misses the tickle. The ball brushes his pads and rolls fine of short fine leg for a leg bye.
Short and on middle, Shai punches it to long on and takes a single.
Darted away from around the wicket, flat and short, Shai Hope goes for the cut but gets beaten on the outside edge.
SIX! Clean strike! Pushed across the right-hander, on the fuller side, Hope plants his front foot across and gets down on a knee. Nails the slog sweep over deep square leg for six more.
Short and on the pads, flicked through mid-wicket for a single by Lewis.
From around the wicket now, short and on off, Hope eases it to long on for a single.
SIX! Will Jacks is greeted with a biggie! Fractionally short, on off, Hope is quick to get deep in his crease, opens his front hip and powers it over mid off for half a dozen.
On a back of a length, on middle, Shai hops back and nudges it wide of mid-wicket for one.
Takes pace off and serves it on a length, on off, Hope pushes it back to Wood.
Drags the length back, on middle and leg, helped twoards short fine leg for a single by Evin.
On middle and leg, on a good length, Shai Hope turns it through square leg for a single to get off the mark.

OUT! TAKEN! 'Catch it' is the cry and Jamie Smith answers the call with a sharp grab! Wood keeps it full, on middle and leg, Johnson Charles clears his front leg and heaves it away on the leg side. Gets it off the inner half of the bat and ends up hitting it flat towards square leg where Smith takes it over his head.
Johnson Charles c J Smith b L Wood 9 (12b 2x4 0x6)
Wood attacks the stumps, very full, Johnson Charles digs it out in front of cover.
Banged in short, over middle, pulled through mid-wicket for a single by JC.
Very full, on off, Johnson Charles squeezes it out down the deck.
FOUR! Johnson Charles makes the Free Hit count! Pitched up, on off and middle, Johnson gets under the ball and pumps it over mid off for a boundary.

NO BALL! This zips through and Brydon Carse gets a good lift off the deck, over middle, Johnson Charles swings to take the short ball on but misses. Given as NO BALL for it being the second bouncer of the over. Free Hit to follow.

FOUR! Johnson Charles finally connects and he is off the mark! Into the wicket by Carse, following the batter. Charles picks up the length early and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Lands it on a back of a length, angling in, on middle and leg, Johnson Charles gets the front leg out of the way and swings to heave it away but misses as the ball sneaks under his bat.
On a hard length, on off, Evin tucks it in front of short fine leg and gets to the other end quickly.
Wood spots JC backing away and he follows him. Charles has a hoick across the line but fails to connect and wears it on the pads.
The length is pulled back now, on middle and leg, Johnson Charles dabs it towards cover-point.
Swing and a miss! Tailing back in, fuller than the previous one. Johnson backs away to go down the ground but the ball beats him on the inside edge.
Shaping back into the right-hander, on the fuller side, Charles clears his front leg and swings across the line. Gets beaten on the inside edge and wears it on the back pad.
Leg bye! On a back of a length, on the pads, Lewis misses out as he looks to nudge it away. Gets it off the pads and a leg bye is taken as the ball rolls towards square leg.
SIX! Evin Lewis and West Indies are on their way! Wood strays on the pads from over the wicket, on a length. Easy pickings for Lewis as he picks it up and over deep backward square leg for a six.
Nails the wide yorker on off, Jacob misses as he looks to squeeze it out.
Lowish full toss, angling in at the pads, Harry Brook gets low and swats it to the right of deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs. England finish with 248 on the board!
SIX! Extraordinary shot from Harry Brook! On a shortish length, on off, Brook backs away and sets up a strong base. Flat bats it down the ground over long off for a biggie.
On a back of a length, outside off, Brook slices it wide of point for a couple of runs.
Lands it full, on off, smashed down the ground to long off for a single by Bethell.
Wide! Takes pace off and pulls the length back but this is beyond the guideline.
Looks for the yorker again but this comes out as a low full toss, outside off, Bethell walks across to swipe it away but misses.
No run.
Full again, angling across, Bethell slices it away to deep point for one.
Wide! Joseph goes searching for the wide yorker but sprays it beyond the guideline.

SIX! Not the cleanest of hits but it will do nicely for Jacob Bethell! That in-between length from Joseph, outside off, Jacob takes a step closer to the line of the ball and pumps it over long on for a six.
On a hard length, on off, steered to deep backward point for a single.

SIX! Harry Brook finally connects! Joseph bangs it in short at pace, around the right shoulder of the batter. Brook gets low enough to get under the ball and scoops it over the keeper's head for a six.
A good short ball from Joseph that keeps climbing onto the batter, Harry Brook looks to hook it away but misses.
On a nagging length, outside off, Harry Brook gives himself too much room and swings for the hills but does not connect.
FOUR! Clever, very clever! Another slower one from Holder, on the fuller side, outside off, Bethell brings out the reverse paddle and plays it fine of the man at short third for a boundary.

Excellent effort from Rovman Powell! Pace off and into the surface, on middle, Jacob Bethell flat bats it down the ground towards long on. Powell sprints to his right near the fence and makes the stop with his right boot, saving a couple of runs for his side.
Executes the yorker to absolute perfection from around the wicket, Jacob Bethell hurriedly gets his bat down but misses as the ball goes through his legs.
Holder pulls his length back and keeps it outside off, Harry walks across to scoop it over short fine leg but the ball gets big on him. Miscues it in front of square leg for one.
Very full, on off, jammed back to the bowler by Brook.

Miscued but Jacob Bethell gets away with it! Holder comes from around the wicket and keeps it near the tramline on off, on a back of a length. Jacob reaches out and slices it over point where Johnson Charles turns around and goes after it. Sherfane Rutherford in the deep does not commit to the catch and jogs in to pick it up eventually. Suddenly, Rutherford pulls up and it seems to be a hamstring issue.
Low full toss fired in, drilled down to long on for a single. 22 runs off Motie's final over.

SIX! Make that a hat-trick of sixes! Motie changes his angle of attack as he comes from around the wicket and pushes it through, on a nagging length, on middle, Jacob hops back in the crease and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket. Gets it over the leaping fielder in the deep for six more.
SIX! Back-to-back sixes for Jacob Bethell! This time, Motie gets the length wrong. A bit too short and it is slower. It sits up to be hit and Bethell slaps it back over the bowler's head for a six.
SIX! Beautifully picked up! Gudakesh Motie errs in line as this is far too straight, on the pads, on a length. Jacob makes use of the angle and swipes it over backward square leg for a six.
Flat and short, on off, Brook slices it over point for a single.
Wide! Tries to sneak it just inside the wide tramline on off, does Motie but he fails to do so. Harry Brook makes the leave.
Full and on off, driven to cover for a single.
A sharp and quick bumper at the batter, Harry Brook gets a bit low and looks to ramp it over the keeper by using the pace but misses.
Big swing and a miss! On a back of a good length, Brook backs away and heaves across the line but gets beaten by the bounce generated by Joseph.
FIVE WIDES! Alzarri Joseph tries to follow Harry Brook again but gets the line wrong. Sprays it well down leg. Brook swings but fails to get any bat on it and the flying Shai Hope stands no chance.

A well-directed bumper, tucking the batter up for room, around the right shoulder, Harry Brook gets it off the splice as he goes for the pull. It lands in front of deep square leg and the batters run two.
Angling away, on a hard length, cut away to deep backward point for a single.

Was that a chance? Given as runs by the umpire, so that's the answer to the question. A tough chance, though. Joseph spots Brook backing away and follows him. On a hard length, Harry looks to whip it away on the leg side. Gets it off the gloves and it goes behind where Shai Hope flings himself to his left but the ball clips him on the fingertips and drops down. A single taken.

FOUR! Innovative and mighty effective! On a back of a length, outside off, Harry Brook walks across his stumps quickly and scoops it over short fine leg. Falls over on his back after completing the shot but the result is all that counts.
Nails the yorker at the toes, Jacob Bethell squeezes it out towards short fine leg. Bethell wants a single but Brook sends him back.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! Clever bowling from Akeal Hosein! Hosein pushes it through, on a fullish length in the line of the leg stump on seeing Ben Duckett making the move towards the off side. Duckett gets down on a knee for the sweep but misses. The ball sneaks past him to clatter into the leg pole. End of a fine knock from Ben. He falls for 84 (46) and England are now 178/3.
Ben Duckett b A Hosein 84 (46b 10x4 2x6)
Tossed up, on middle and leg, Brook skips down the track and lofts it on the bounce to long on for one.

Chance? Lowish full toss, on off, Ben Duckett gets low to smash it down the ground. Duckett manages to get enough elevation to clear Akeal Hosein. The ball sails over the head of Akeal for a couple of runs.
Very full, on middle, Ben Duckett jams it out in the vacant mid-wicket region and comes charging back for the second run.
Speared in, full and on the pads, Brook works it away to wide long on for a run.
Nails the yorker at the base of the off stump. Brook hurriedly gets his bat down and slips a bit in the process. Squeezes it to point for one.
FOUR! Nicely done! On a hard length, at pace, on middle, Brook backs away and opens the bat face. Uses the pace to steer it wide of backward point for a boundary.
Full, pace off, wide outside off, Ben Duckett drives it to covers for a single.
Fuller, well wide outside off, Ben Duckett cannot reach it, and WIDE called.
Slower one, down the leg-side, Ben Duckett tries to scoop but misses it. WIDED!
FOUR! Pace off delivery from Sherfane Rutherford, short length, outside off, Ben Duckett cuts it nicely behind deep backward point. Evin Lewis once again dives but does not manage to stop the ball.
Short, angling away from the batter, Ben Duckett cuts it to deep point where Evin Lewis dives to stop the ball. Two runs taken.
Starts with fuller, wide outside off, Ben Duckett drags that one straight to the extra cover fielder.
Shorter and quicker, on off, Harry Brook cuts it straight to backward point. Back-to-back quiet overs for West Indies!
Very full, on the pads, turned away in front of square on the leg side for another single.
Short and on middle, punched to long on for one more by Harry.
Motie tries to push it through but ends up bowling a full toss, flat batted down to long on for a run by Ben.
On the pads, Brook works it to deep mid-wicket and gets off the mark with a single.
Full and on the pads, Ben flicks it to deep backward square leg for one.

OUT! CAUGHT! The introduction of Sherfane Rutherford has paid off for the West Indies. Full length, wide outside off, Jos Buttler shuffles across the off stump and goes aerial over covers but doesn't get much elevation. Shimron Hetmyer, standing there, takes a good catch to remove Jos Buttler. Six runs and the big wicket of Buttler in that over.
Jos Buttler (wk) c S Hetmyer b S Rutherford 22 (10b 1x4 2x6)
Full length, just outside off, Ben Duckett drives that one through covers for a single.
Takes pace off and it is on the fuller side, outside off, Jos Buttler swings too early and mishits it to long on for a run.
On a nagging length, around off, Duckett flays it to deep backward point for one.
Another one from Rutherford kept away from the batter, Jos reaches out and cuts it to deep point for one. It would have been a wide had Buttler left it.
Wide! Sprayed beyond the wide guideline on off. Jos lets it be. 150 up for England!
Pushed across the left-hander, on a length, Duckett slices it to deep point for a single.
SIX! Jos on the charge! Fuller, sliding on the leg stump, Jos Buttler skips down the track using his feet, and smashes it over deep mid-wicket for a maximum. 13 runs from the over.
Fuller, outside-off, Ben Duckett sweeps it to square leg for a single.

FOUR! Akeal Hosein drops that one short, outside off, Ben Duckett sees the length and pulls that one towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder there runs to his right to stop that one, but can't get to the ball as it races to the fence for a four.
Fuller, on the leg stump, Jos Buttler clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Shortish, outside off, Ben Duckett works it to long on for a single.
Lands it short, on the off stump, Ben Duckett hits this one straight to the cover fielder.

FOUR! Not where he intended it to go, but they all count! Joseph follows the batter and serves this full and outside off. Jos Buttler shuffles across for the scoop but gets cramped up as the ball goes off the top edge towards the third man fence for a boundary. Simon Doull informs on air that this is England's best 10-over score in T20Is.

SIX! That is outta here! Alzarri Joseph hits the length hard and on middle, angling in a bit. Jos Buttler moves across to get inside the line of the ball and shovels it over the fine leg fence for a biggie.
Good length, wide outside off, Ben Duckett reaches out for it and cuts it to point for a single.
Short, outside off. the ball gets big on Jos Buttler and he fends it to mid-wicket for a run.
A bit fuller from the previous delivery, wide outside off, Ben Duckett throws his hands to it and plays it to cover for a single.
Starts from over the wicket, back of a length, angling into the batter, Jos Buttler hits it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Fuller, sliding on the pads, Jos Buttler guides it towards long on for a single. 8 runs and a wicket from the over!

OUT! TAKEN IN THE DEEP! Gudakesh Motie finally gets the first breakthrough for West Indies. Something to cheer about for the visitors. This one is dragged back, on middle. Jamie Smith rocks and looks to smash it over mid-wicket, but just fails to get the distance on this one as he hits it from the bottom half of the bat. It goes high in the air towards deep mid-wicket, where Shimron Hetmyer settles under it near the ropes and pouches it safely. Smith departs after a smashing 60 off 26, and the huge 120-run opening stand is broken now.
Jamie Smith c S Hetmyer b G Motie 60 (26b 4x4 5x6)
Slows it down, full and on off, swept through square leg for a single.
Fired in, very full, at the stumps, Duckett drills it down the ground where Romario Shepherd sprints and slides to his right at long on and cuts it off. Another couple of runs.
Tossed up, full and on off, Ben sweeps it to the right of deep backward square leg for another brace.
From over the wicket, fuller, outside off. Ben Duckett comes down the track and tucks it wide of long on for a couple.

DROPPED! Shimron Hetmyer has put it down, and how costly will it be for the West Indies? Fuller, wide outside off, Jamie Smith goes hard after it as he looks to loft it over extra cover, but doesn't get the connection right. Shimron Hetmyer looks to take it over his head but the ball bursts through his hands. Two runs taken.

SIX MORE! Best of the lot! Bangs this one hard into the surface, outside off. Jamie Smith stays in his crease and leg side of the ball. He extends his arms to reach out for it and slaps it over the deep extra cover fence for the third six in the over. Nothing is bothering these two!

SIX! FIFTY FOR SMITH! A fiery half-century from the youngster. He gets to his maiden T20I fifty in just 23 balls, and this is looking really threatening for the Windies. Goes fuller and on middle, angling in a bit. This is in the slot and Smith does not miss out as he tonks it over the long on fence again for half a dozen more. Also, 100 up for England!
Romario Shepherd goes fuller, wide outside off. Jamie Smith reaches out for it but doesn't get any bat onto it.

SIX! Stand and deliver! Short of a length and just around off, Jamie Smith just stands tall, gets right on top of the bounce and swats it over the long on fence for a biggie. Jason Holder is there but he had no chance.
Starts from over the wicket, on back of a length, on the leg stump. Ben Duckett pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Fuller, outside off. Jamie Smith comes down the track and hits it back to the bowler.

SIX! Clears the fence! Jamie Smith is not holding back either! Flighted, full and on leg. Smith goes down on one knee and heaves it away. He does not get it from the middle of the bat and the fielder at deep mid-wicket thinks he is in the game. However, the wind takes it sailing over his head for a biggie.
Almost a yorker, outside off, Jamie Smith looks to squeeze it but doesn't get any connection.
Fuller, outside off. Ben Duckett gets down on a knee and sweeps it to square leg for one.
Switches to around the wicket, shortish, on the stumps. Jamie Smith works from the back foot to long on for a single.
Starts from over the wicket, fuller, on the off stump, Ben Duckett tucks it to mid on for a single.

FIFTY FOR DUCKETT! This has been a scintillating knock from him as he gets to it in just 20 balls. It is also the joint 4th fastest for an English batter in this format. A slower low full toss, on middle, Ben Duckett knocks it towards mid on for one. England are 83 for no loss at the end of the Powerplay!
FOUR! Oh..wow! Top shot! Jason Holder bangs this one into the pitch, on off. Ben Duckett stays leg side of the ball, rides the bounce and ramps it over short third for four more runs.
Gets the yorker right this time, on off, Ben Duckett makes room but only manages to dig it out to the off side.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Short of a length and just outside off, Ben Duckett backs away a bit, frees his arms and crunches it over point for another boundary.
Pitched up and on middle, Jamie Smith flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Class written all over it! Fuller one and on middle, Jamie Smith presents the full face of the bat and plays a fabulous on drive as the ball races to the long on fence for a boundary.

FOUR! SMASHED! Save your heads! Good length and on middle, Ben Duckett backs away and flat-bats it really hard down the pitch. Alzarri Joseph on his follow-through, gets his right thumb on it, but it just does not stick. It evades the umpire and races to the fence for another boundary. Maybe half a chance, but a tough one. 18 runs off the over.
FOUR! Superb batting! Alzarri Joseph goes for the yorker, outside off. Ben Duckett shuffles across early, takes it on the full and scoops it towards the fine leg fence for another boundary.
Falls short! Hits the length hard again, on middle, Ben Duckett mistimes his pull as the ball drops just in front of mid-wicket.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Short of a length and on the sixth stump line. Ben Duckett lets it come to him, opens the face of the bat and uses the pace to steer it through point for a boundary.
Back of a length and around off, Ben Duckett stabs it towards extra covers.

SIX! Welcome to the game, Alzarri Joseph! He bangs this one into the pitch, on middle, sits up nicely for the batter. Ben Duckett stands tall, gets on top of it and whacks it over the deep square leg fence for a flat six.
FOUR! 50 up for England in no time! A slower one, full and on middle, Jamie Smith gets deceived by the lack of pace but still manages to lift it well over mid on for four more runs.
SIX! BOOM! Romario Shepherd sticks to shorter length and on middle. Jamie Smith picks up the length early and pulls it nicely over the deep mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Short of a length and around off, Jamie Smith tries to go over covers again, but this time slices it a bit. He just gets it over the fielder for a brace.

FOUR! Threads the gap beautifully! Romario Shepherd goes a bit fuller and around middle. Jamie Smith gives himself some room to access the off side and carves it between cover and extra cover for a boundary.
Hits the length hard but down the leg, Ben Duckett helps it towards fine leg for a run.
Back of a length and on middle, Jamie Smith flat-bats it wide of mid on for a single.
Fires one full and on middle, Ben Duckett gets low and swipes it to mid-wicket. 17 runs off the over!
FOUR! Excellent use of the feet! Flatter, full and just outside off. Ben Duckett dances down the track, extends his arms to reach for it and thumps it past the bowler for four more runs.

SIX! Incredible shot! He is playing with the field now! There was a deep backward square leg before Duckett hit the first boundary in this over. This one is tossed up, full and around off. Ben Duckett goes down across well and slog-sweeps it powerfully over the same region for a biggie.

In the air....safe! Flighted, full and on middle, Ben Duckett skips down the track and lofts it but fails to get a hold of this one. The ball goes up in the air and well over mid on as Evin Lewis chases after it and flicks it back just in time to keep it down to two.
FOUR! Nicely played! Floated, full and on middle, Ben Duckett crouches a bit low but keeps his front leg out of the way, and slogs it to the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Quicker one, low full toss around off, Jamie Smith tries to drive it but gets an inside edge towards square leg for a single.
Short of a length and on middle, angling in, Jamie Smith gets a bit hurried and mistimes his pull shot towards deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Up and over! Pitched up and just on off. Jamie Smith gets right underneath it and with the full flow of the bat lofts it well over mid on for his first boundary.
On a length and on leg, Ben Duckett nudges it through square leg for a run.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off, Jamie Smith drives it on the up towards sweeper covers for a single.
Touch fuller and around off, Jamie Smith pushes it nicely through covers for a couple of runs.
Jason Holder begins with a good-length delivery, on off, shaping in a bit, Jamie Smith blocks it down the pitch.

FOUR! Unorthodox but effective! Akeal Hosein gives this one a little bit more flight, full and on middle and leg. Ben Duckett has already decided to go for the switch-hit early. He gets into a good position and smacks it over extra covers for the first boundary of the game.
Pushed through quicker, short and on middle, nips back in sharply as this is the arm ball, Jamie Smith moves back and flicks it off the inside half of the bat through mid-wicket for another run.
Darts this one full and on middle, Ben Duckett drills it to long on for a run.
Flighted, full and on middle and off, drifts away, Ben Duckett knocks it down the pitch.
England and Jamie Smith are underway! Tossed up, full and on middle, Jamie Smith tucks it wide of mid on for a single.
Akeal Hosein starts with a floated delivery, full and on off, Jamie Smith strides out and pushes it to short covers.
